    <text>
        <body><div type="bibliography">
                
                <p><bibl><ptr target="#fraser1958"/>, pp. 113-115, n. <citedRange>7</citedRange>, pl. XIII, 7</bibl>, whence 
                    <bibl><ptr target="#SEG"/>, <citedRange>18.730</citedRange></bibl> (only side a);
                    <bibl><ptr target="#gpc1961"/>,  p. 31, n. <citedRange>11</citedRange>, figs. 21-22 (from †Oliverio's papers)</bibl>, whence 
                    <bibl><ptr target="#SEG"/>, <citedRange>20.725</citedRange></bibl>;
                    <bibl><ptr target="#IGCyr"/> <citedRange>063000</citedRange></bibl>.
                    Cf. <bibl><ptr target="#bagnall1972"/><citedRange/></bibl>;
                    <bibl><ptr target="#mooren1975"/>, n. <citedRange>0372</citedRange></bibl>;
                    <bibl><ptr target="#mooren1977"/>, pp. <citedRange>186-188</citedRange></bibl>;
                    <bibl><ptr target="#hauben1977"/><citedRange/></bibl>; 
                    <bibl><ptr target="#laronde1987"/>, pp. <citedRange>445-446, 462</citedRange></bibl>, whence 
                    <bibl><ptr target="#SEG"/>, <citedRange>38.1899</citedRange></bibl>;
                    <bibl><ptr target="#criscuolo2011"/>, p. <citedRange>137, footnote 22</citedRange></bibl>;
                    <bibl><ptr target="#rosamilia2014"/>, n. <citedRange>9</citedRange> and fig. 9</bibl> (for the re-use).</p>
            </div><div type="edition" xml:lang="grc" xml:space="preserve">
                                        
                            <ab>
                            <lb n="1"/><w lemma="βασιλεύς">Βασιλέα</w> <persName type="ruler" key="Ptolemy IX"><name nymRef="#Πτολεμαῖος">Πτολεμαῖον</name>
                            <lb n="2"/><rs type="epithet" key="Theos Soter"><w lemma="θεός">θεὸν</w> <w lemma="σωτήρ">Σωτῆρα</w></rs></persName> τὸν <w lemma="ἐκ">ἐγ</w> <w lemma="βασιλεύς">βασιλέως</w>
                            <lb n="3"/><persName type="ruler" key="Ptolemy VIII"><name nymRef="#Πτολεμαῖος">Πτολεμαίου</name> 
                                τοῦ <rs type="epithet" key="Euergetes II"><num type="ordinal" value="2"><w lemma="δεύτερος">δευτέρου</w></num> <w lemma="εὐεργέτης">Εὐεργέτου</w></rs></persName>
                            <lb n="4"/><persName type="attested" key=""><name nymRef="#Στόλος">Στόλος</name></persName> <rs type="aulic" key="ton proton philon">τῶν <w lemma="πρῶτος">πρώτων</w> <w lemma="φίλος">φίλων</w></rs> καὶ <rs type="office" key="archedeatros"><w lemma="ἀρχεδέατρος">ἀρχεδέατρος</w></rs>
                            <lb n="5"/><w lemma="εὔνοια">εὐνοίας</w> <w lemma="ἕνεκεν">ἕνεκεν</w> τῆς <w lemma="εἰς">εἰς</w> <w lemma="ἑαυτοῦ">αὑτόν</w>.
                        </ab>
                        
            </div><div type="apparatus" xml:space="preserve">
            
                <p/>
 </div><div type="translation" xml:lang="fr" xml:space="preserve">
            <p><supplied reason="subaudible">Statue du</supplied> roi Ptolémée, Dieu Sôter, fils du roi Ptolémée second Evergète <supplied reason="subaudible">consacrée</supplied> 
                par Stolos, des Premiers Amis, archedeatros <supplied reason="explanation">intendant en chef</supplied>, en raison de sa générosité à son égard.</p>
         </div><div type="translation" xml:lang="en" xml:space="preserve">
            <p><supplied reason="subaudible">Statue of</supplied> king Ptolemy, God Soter, son of king Ptolemy the second Euergetes <supplied reason="subaudible">dedicated</supplied> 
                by Stolos, of the First Friends, archedeatros <supplied reason="explanation">chief stewart</supplied>, on behalf of his well-doing towards himself.</p>
            </div><div type="translation" xml:lang="it" xml:space="preserve">
            <p><supplied reason="subaudible">Statua del</supplied> re Tolemeo, Dio Sotere, figlio del re Tolemeo Evergete secondo, <supplied reason="subaudible">dedicata</supplied> 
                da Stolos, dei Primi Amici, archedeatros <supplied reason="explanation">capo maggiordomo</supplied>, in considerazione della benevolenza nei suoi confronti.</p>
         </div>
            <div type="translation" xml:space="preserve" xml:lang="ar">
                <p>(تمثال) الملك بتوليميوس (بطليموس)، المُؤلَّه المُنْقِذ، ابن الملك بتوليميوس إفيريغيتس الثاني، (نُصِبَ) من قبل ستولوس، من الاصدقاء الأوائل (أحد أعضاء هذه المجموعة)،  أرخيدياتروس (كبير الخدم أو مدير الأعمال)، لما تفضل به من خير (أي الملك) عليه أو عرفانًا بفضلة.</p>
            </div>
            <div type="commentary">
                
                <p>The base was re-used and the artist's signature related to the first use was not erased. However, as it stood at the rear of the base and as its letters were
                upside down, it should not be mentioned as a part of the present monument.</p>
                <p>This inscription and <ref type="inscription" source="#IGCyr2">IGCyr015900</ref>, both in very good condition, have allowed to restore another dedication by Stolos erected in the port 
                    of Cyrene (<ref type="inscription" source="#IGCyr2">IGCyr102500</ref>).</p>
                <p>On Stolos, the Athenian admiral, see <bibl><ptr target="#bagnall1972"/></bibl>, who proposed for the Cyrenaean dedications a date between 108 and 103 BC; 
                    <bibl><ptr target="#hauben1977"/></bibl>, who explored the possibility that he was a born a Cyrenaean and granted Athenian citizenship. On behalf of his aulic title
                    and office <bibl><ptr target="#mooren1977"/>, pp. <citedRange>186-188</citedRange></bibl> dated this inscription to 108 BC, somewhat earlier 
                    in the year than <ref type="inscription" source="#IGCyr2">IGCyr015900</ref>, where he is also 'in charge of the reins'.</p>
	           <p>The findspot and date of discovery are known from a recently published report of excavations (see <bibl><ptr target="#luni2014b"/>, p. <citedRange>153</citedRange></bibl>).
	               Quite normally, honours for the king were exposed on the agora.</p>
	<p/>
            </div></body>
